ir 0.1.0 — self-describing R scripts

USAGE:
    ir run [Rscript-options...] [--isolated] [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] <script.R> [args...]
    ir run [Rscript-options...] [--isolated] [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] -e <expr> [args...]
    ir tool run [Rscript-options...] [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] --from <pkg-ref> <command> [args...]
    ir tool run [Rscript-options...] [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] <pkg-ref> [args...]
    ir tool install [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] [--bin-dir <dir>] [--force] <pkg-ref>
    ir cache <command>

`ir run` reads the YAML frontmatter from <script.R>, resolves its
dependencies, builds a dedicated package library, and runs the script
against it. With -e it evaluates inline R expressions instead of a file.
`ir tool run` resolves a package ref and runs an executable from that
package's exec directory. `ir tool install` writes PATH launchers for
the supported executables in a package's exec directory. --with adds
dependencies on the command line, and --r-version selects the R version
with rig. Leading Rscript options are passed to Rscript for script and
tool run targets; trailing args are passed through to the program.
`ir cache` manages the dependency resolution and materialised library cache.

ENVIRONMENT:
    IR_CACHE_DIR   override the cache dir (default: tools::R_user_dir("ir", "cache"))
    IR_RSCRIPT     path to the Rscript executable (default: Rscript on PATH)
